  "text": "Hospitalizations for COPD exacerbations have increased significantly over the past 10 years. [CITATION_1] In the USA, rates of hospital discharges from 2001 to 2012, emergency department visits from 2006 to 2011, and the 30-day readmission rate from 2009 to 2012 did not change significantly among patients with COPD. In contrast, significant reductions in length of stay were reported. [CITATION_2] The authors reported a decline in mean length of hospital stay from 4.5 days in 2001 to 4.0 days in 2012 among hospitalized COPD patients. [CITATION_3] In the current study, length of hospital stay was found to be longer in noneosinophilic COPD exacerbations than eosinophilic ones.",
